The station gets called to a train accident where a teenager is caught beneath an axle. The teen is more concerned for his missing sister, whom Peter finds mangled to death a few hundreds yards away. The team is able to recover from the discovery, but Mills cannot. He is given the rest of the day off to ponder his future at his family's restaurant. Casey takes Mills to visit a family Casey saved years ago to show him the benefits of the job. Casey got the idea from two visiting Canadian firefighters, with whom Mouch seems to have a problem. Meanwhile, Shay and Dawson must deal with a domestic situation that Dawson appears to make worse.

The crew arrives at the Vaughns' upscale home to put out a kitchen fire and the owner's expensive necklace goes missing. The CFD internal affairs bureau investigate those that were there to put out the fire. Casey stands by his men, and Otis investigates the Vaughns. He discovers they were in financial trouble—the fire and theft could have been an insurance fraud. Casey dupes Mrs. Vaughn into believing the cameras on their helmets recorded something and he is prepared to inform the police. His team later gets news that the necklace has been found. The crew is also called to an apartment fire and Cruz believes his brother Leon may be inside. He finds gang leader Flaco alive and leaves him to perish in the fire, announcing an "all clear". Shay discovers Severide has been taking pills to alleviate his shoulder pain and decides to stay with Dawson. As she and Dawson restock the ambulance, it is hit by a tow truck.

The ambulance crash sends Shay to the hospital with a traumatic brain injury. She regains consciousness, but Severide is distraught over how things have recently been between them. Shay at first insists staying with Dawson is the best thing for her, but changes her mind when he admits his shoulder injury. Leon discovers that Cruz let gang leader Flaco die in the fire, but both agree to keep the news a secret. Casey visits his imprisoned mother, who is up for parole. She asks him to speak kindly at the parole meeting. He asks his sister to do the same, but she refuses, not forgiving her mother for killing their father. Finally, Dawson had cooked Shay a homecoming dinner, but invites Mills over after Shay's recent decision. Friendly chatter turns romantic and they make out on the floor.

Severide finally addresses Chief Boden about his injury and makes some important personal decisions about his future. Meanwhile, Casey struggles with family matters and Dawson takes matters into her own hands when she discovers a young girl who is the sole survivor at the scene of a rescue call. Herrmann decides to end his limousine company and the limousine becomes a training vehicle for the Chicago Fire Department Academy. Herrmann later announces to the team that his wife is pregnant with their fifth child.

As Antonio recovers from the shooting, Dawson visits Voight in prison to ask about the gang activity. She is told to look for someone named "T.T." but is now obligated to help Voight. She finds T.T. who threatens her with a gun to never return. Casey learns Dawson visited Voight and is upset with her. Later, T.T. sends a girl to visit to Dawson. She wants to testify against the ones who shot Antonio. Casey's mother finally confesses to him that she killed his father for something he said about Casey. Whaley insists Severide contact his sister Renée. Severide tracks down his ex-fiance, who is now working as a stripper and doesn't want anything to do with him. Whaley later finds out that Renée overdosed and was rushed to the hospital. He calls Severide to tell him the news.

Cruz puts himself and his fellow firefighters in jeopardy as a building's roof collapses after he was told not to enter to save a trapped dog. Casey wants Cruz's badge. When Mouch finally gets the truth out of Cruz, he vouches for him and Casey allows Cruz to keep his job. Severide finally gets through to his ex-fiancée Renée after she is released from a psychiatric ward. Casey and his sister Christie's constant bickering forces their mother move out. A lawyer tells Shay and Clarice that they need their own place to gain custody of the baby. Shay finds a place, but Clarice tells her that she has made a deal with her ex-husband about split-custody. The catch: Clarice must move to New York with them and they must leave that night.

Severide finally gets through to his ex-fiancée Renée after she is released from a psychiatric ward. Casey and his sister Christie's constant bickering forces their mother move out. A lawyer tells Shay and Clarice that they need their own place to gain custody of the baby. Shay finds a place, but Clarice tells her that she has made a deal with her ex-husband about split-custody. The catch: Clarice must move to New York with them and they must leave that night.

Old emotional wounds are opened when Lieutenant Severide’s father Benny comes to town and clashes with Chief Boden over the death of their former colleague. Mills helps a distraught driver who caused an accident and Shay makes a decision about her future with Clarice. Meanwhile, Herrmann, Otis and Dawson get to the bottom of a mystery about their bar.

data: Selfridge is in a coma from the car crash. Ellen Love is recovering from a botched suicide attempt by drug overdose. Mr Grove– recently bereaved– returns from leave to take charge and his first decision is to ban Lady Mae's suffragettes from meeting in the store. Lady Mae has begun an affair with Victor and he is cold to Agnes; Henri Leclair would like to become her suitor. Selfridge's young son Gordon goes alone to the store, learning he alone will inherit it someday. Ellen thinks about selling her story to the press but is forestalled by an offer from Frank Edwards. The staff must appease the angry suffragettes.

The contestants are challenged to create "comfort" dishes. Lauren of Team Nigella wins the first team challenge, giving her team an advantage during the individual task. Lauren, Micah, Renatta, and Shawn find themselves in the bottom four, as the four judges have given them all one red star, declaring them as the creators of the four worst dishes of the round. Khristianne and Sarah both receive one gold star, meaning that they created one of the judges' favorite dishes, while Diane receives two gold stars. Lauren is automatically save, as she had won immunity for herself by winning the team challenger earlier. Shawn is spared and Micah and Renatta are the first cooks sent home.

Gregg is declared safe, as he held immunity. One contestant is to be eliminated after Andrés does the judging. The mentors help their team to try to ensure their placement in the final three. data: February 1924. Nucky, preferring to stay in his room up in the Albatross Hotel and away from the boardwalk, comes to a peace agreement with Masseria and Rothstein. Richard, on his way home to reunite with his sister, leaves some corpses in his wake. Gillian, still an addict but desperate to get her grandson back, is resorting to prostitution until a stranger shows up with a better offer. Revenue Agent Sawicki's new partner, Warren Knox, isn't as naive as he acts. Chalky tries to coolly run the Onyx Club, but his right-hand man, Dunn Pursley, gets into a mess of trouble with a booking-agent and his wife.

Rothstein's way of dealing with his bad luck at the card table leads Nucky to make Lansky his partner in the Florida scheme. After a night on the town with Ralph Capone, Eddie pays for it in the morning when he's arrested by Knox.

Knox torments Eddie and reveals his dark past, pushing him to betrayal. Willie, arrested over the death of schoolmate Henry Gaines, phones Nucky. Gillian, desperate to regain custody of Tommy but losing her grip, turns to Dunn for a fix. Van Alden's enlisted by Frank and Al Capone to bust some Democrat supporters' heads; Frank's gunned down by deputized Chicago agents. Nucky has Willie stick to a false alibi, pays off the Philadelphia DA to free him, and leaves him with some avuncular advice shortly before Willie's roommate is arrested for Gaines' death. Eddie, back at the Albatross and guilt-ridden about betraying Nucky's trust, jumps out of his window to his death.

Tolliver hears about Willie's evasion of the law and pursues Eli as his means to ending Nucky's empire. Chalky busts up one of Narcisse's drug houses, with two-faced Dunn along for the show. Nucky's unpleasantly surprised when Sally rides up to Atlantic City with the new bootlegging delivery from Tampa. Narcisse employs Daughter Maitland to way-lay Chalky, but she can't bring herself to let Dunn kill Chalky and she stabs Dunn fatally in the back instead.

title: ... Gustavsen continues to be a marvel of economical invention, a player who speaks little but says much. Restored, Returned is a logical extension/expansion on his previous ECM releases, as his nuanced, tender playing eschews stereotypical references to Norwegian music as icy or cool, even as "The Way In" cinematically traverses imaginary bodies of water explored regularly by pianist Ketil Bjørnstad. But with more colors at his disposal and a greater attention to song form—even as the result feels somehow freer—Gustavsen has shaped an album even more appealing in its subtle but unmistakable experimentation...
